# Monorepo Cursor Rules (Turborepo / pnpm workspaces)

## Structure
- `apps/` — deployable applications (web, api, mobile)
- `packages/` — shared code (ui, utils, config, types)
- `tooling/` — shared tooling config (eslint, tsconfig, jest)
- Each package has its own `package.json` and `tsconfig.json`

## Dependency Rules
- Apps can import from packages
- Packages must NOT import from apps
- Cross-package imports via package name (not relative paths): `import { Button } from "@repo/ui"`
- Internal packages use `"main": "./src/index.ts"` with `publishConfig` for dist

## TypeScript
- Root `tsconfig.json` with `references` to each package
- Each package extends from `@repo/typescript-config`
- `declaration: true` and `declarationMap: true` in all packages

## Turborepo Tasks
- `build` depends on `^build` (dependencies build first)
- `test` depends on `^build`
- `lint` and `typecheck` run independently
- Use `turbo run build --filter=...` for targeted builds

## Package Naming
- `@repo/<name>` internal convention
- Descriptive names: `@repo/ui`, `@repo/auth`, `@repo/database`
- No `utils` catch-all — be specific (`@repo/formatting`, `@repo/validation`)
